Ri referred to a joint statement issued by Kim Jong Un and Donald Trump at the first summit of a sitting U.S. President and a North Korean leader in Singapore on 12 June, where Kim promised to work towards the "decommissioning of nuclear weapons on the Korean peninsula" while Trump promised guarantees for the security of North Korea.
North Korea has applied for a formal end to the Korean war 1950-53, but the United States has said that Pyongyang must first dismantle its nuclear weapons.
Washington has also refused negotiations to ease international sanctions against North Korea.
"USA insists on "decommissioning first" and increases pressure through sanctions to achieve its purpose by force and even objecting to "the declaration to end the war", says Ri.
"The notion that sanctions can get us on our knees is a wish dream for those people who lack knowledge of us.
